{
  "text": "The production of reactive oxygen species (ROS) is a significant factor in the neuropathology of stroke [CITATION_1] . During acute ischemic stroke, ROS can be generated through multiple injury mechanisms, including mitochondrial inhibition, Ca 2+ overload and reperfusion injury [CITATION_2] . H 2 O 2 is the source of HO· radicals, which can contribute to neuronal injury after cerebral ischemic reperfusion, resulting in neuronal death [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The hydroxyl radical-scavenging activity of TRCQT was directly evaluated using an ESR method, and the results revealed that TRCQT scavenged HO· radicals in a concentration-dependent manner.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "45112382",
